        jTextArea1.setText("JavaScript.\nUsed to create visual effects on the page.\nCan also be used for simple data handling. \nOther programming languages can be used e.g. python and java.\nHowever, JavaScript is preferred as it is lightweight.\n\nCascading Style Sheet.\nIt is used for visual presentation, formatting and  layout.\nSimple animations can be done using CSS. \nMore complex animations have be done using a \nprogramming or scripting language.\n\nHyper Text Markup Language.\nUsed to define the general structure of the webpage.\nHTML5 is the current standard for webpages.\nCan be typed in a plaintext editor e.g. Notepad\nHowever some text editors are built to provide code assistance for HTML e.g. Notepad++, Sublime Text and Brackets.\n\n\n");
